<TITLE> Spain's Puyol injures foot in 2-1 win </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 INNSBRUCK, June 15 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Spain centre back Carles Puyol injured his foot during the 2-1 win over Sweden in Euro 2008 Group D on Saturday. The Spanish Federation said the defender, who was replaced by Raul Albiol in the 24th minute, would undergo tests on Sunday to assess the seriousness of the injury. Coach Luis Aragones said midfielders Xavi and David Silva had also picked up minor knocks. "If we qualify I may take the chance to look over some other players and rest others like Silva who has a problem with his toe nail but we'll have to wait and see," Aragones told a news conference
